{"word":"ριζόω","slug":"ριζόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ριζόω</b></el> <el>(ριζόω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ρίζα'><el>ρίζα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make to strike root</i>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to root in the ground, plant</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>ἐρρίζωσε τὴν τυραννίδα</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to take root, strike root</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to be rooted, firmly fixed</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> also of land, <i>to be planted with trees</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}